{"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"title":"Texture2DArray","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"class","roleHeading":"Class","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Texture2DArray"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Texture2DArray"}],"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot14Texture2DArrayC","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Texture2DArray","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A single texture resource which consists of multiple, separate images. Each image has the same dimensions and number of mipmap levels."}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Texture2DArray\/createPlaceholder()"],"title":"Instance Methods"},{"anchor":"Type-Properties","title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Texture2DArray\/godotClassName"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Texture2DArray"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Texture2DArray is different from a Texture3D: The Texture2DArray does not support trilinear interpolation between the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Image"},{"type":"text","text":"s, i.e. no blending. See also "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Cubemap","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CubemapArray"},{"type":"text","text":", which are texture arrays with specialized cubemap functions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A Texture2DArray is also different from an ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AtlasTexture","isActive":true},{"text":": In a Texture2DArray, all images are treated separately. In an atlas, the regions (i.e. the single images) can be of different sizes. Furthermore, you usually need to add a padding around the regions, to prevent accidental UV mapping to more than one region. The same goes for mipmapping: Mipmap chains are handled separately for each layer. In an atlas, the slicing has to be done manually in the fragment shader.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create such a texture file yourself, reimport your image files using the Godot Editor import presets."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ImageTextureLayered"]},{"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SQ","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SH","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantStorable"]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/texture2darray"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/s23CustomStringConvertibleP":{"type":"unresolvable","title":"Swift.CustomStringConvertible","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Lang